data.name: chkTruncateExtra4206Samples.ToolTip
data.value: Some erroneous FLAC encoders add extra 4608 zero samples at the end of each file. These extra samples can be detected and removed.

data.name: chkFillUpCUE.Text
data.value: Fill up missing CUE data from tags

data.name: chkEmbedLog.Text
data.value: Embed log file as a tag

data.name: chkEmbedLog.ToolTip
data.value: File should be in the same directory as source file and have a .log extension

data.name: chkAutoCorrectFilenames.ToolTip
data.value: Preprocess with filename corrector if unable to locate audio files

data.name: chkPreserveHTOA.Text
data.value: Preserve HTOA for gaps appended output

data.name: chkArFixOffset.Text
data.value: Fix offset if % of verified tracks >=

data.name: chkWriteArTagsOnConvert.ToolTip
data.value: Add ACCURATERIPCOUNT/ACCURATERIPCOUNTALLOFFSETS/ACCURATERIPTOTAL tags to output files. You can set up foobar2000 to show those values, and see if your music was ripped correctly or how popular it is.

data.name: chkArNoUnverifiedAudio.Text
data.value: Encode only if % of verified tracks >=

data.name: chkFilenamesANSISafe.ToolTip
data.value: Only allow characters, which are present in ANSI codepage, for compatibility with non-unicode applications

data.name: chkWriteARTagsOnVerify.ToolTip
data.value: Add ACCURATERIPCOUNT/ACCURATERIPCOUNTALLOFFSETS/ACCURATERIPTOTAL tags to input files. You can set up foobar2000 to show those values, and see if your music was ripped correctly or how popular it is.

data.name: chkHDCDDecode.ToolTip
data.value: HDCD decoding is irreversable. Resulting files cannot be burned to the CD. 24-bit audio files are created, but the actual resolution is 20 bit

data.name: chkHDCDStopLooking.ToolTip
data.value: Stop looking for HDCD information, If none found in first 10 seconds of the disc

data.name: chkHDCD24bit.ToolTip
data.value: When not using lossyWAV, extend to 24 bit for compatibility

data.name: chkHDCDLW16.ToolTip
data.value: When converting to lossyWAV, truncate to 16 bit
